        <mxCell id="p4e16" edge="1" parent="1" source="b53" target="p4pwr" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;html=1;strokeColor=#b85450;fontSize=10;dashed=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" value="9V rail"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4e17" edge="1" parent="1" source="p4pwr" target="p4pico" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;html=1;strokeColor=#b85450;fontSize=10;dashed=1;exitX=0;exitY=0.5;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=1;entryY=0.9;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" value="+5V VSYS"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4note1" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;fontSize=11;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacing=8;dashed=1;" value="v4 PICO ARCHITECTURE NOTES (2026-07-18)&#10;&#10;WHAT MOVED TO FIRMWARE (Pico):&#10;- Both LFOs: 16 wavetable waveforms. Bank A: ramp up, ramp&#10;  down, square, triangle, sine, sweep, random slopes, random&#10;  levels (S&amp;H). Bank B: Lorenz, Rossler, drunk walk, Perlin&#10;  drift, wobble, glitch + 2 open slots (white/pink noise are&#10;  candidates - Jason auditioning in sim v0.11 now).&#10;- Tap tempo + waveform select per LFO (footswitch gestures,&#10;  Jason&#39;s spec: &lt;800ms tap / &gt;1.3s hold-cycle / dead zone).&#10;- Gate timing (THRESH/HOLD/FADE) - LED+LDR stays as the&#10;  analog audio element, Pico just drives the LED.&#10;- CV routing matrix: target select, strength, slew - kills&#10;  both rotary switches + CV trim pots (now firmware).&#10;- Waveform/target selection saved to Pico flash (survives&#10;  power-off).&#10;&#10;WHAT STAYED ANALOG (unchanged from v3):&#10;- Entire audio path: buffer, 40Hz HP, gain stage, LM567 core,&#10;  Bazz Fuss, MIX, LM13700 SVF, gate LDR, 60Hz HP, 800Hz bell,&#10;  output buffer, true-bypass. VREF 4.5V scheme unchanged.&#10;- Envelope follower rectifier (Pico reads its output on ADC1).&#10;&#10;BOM DELTA vs v3:&#10;- OUT: 2x STOMPLFO (7.50), LM393, 2x rotary target switch&#10;  (~8), 4x CV trim pot, 2x PDM filter op-amp stages.&#10;- IN: Pico (~5), CD4051 (~0.30), 4x WS2812D-F5 (~0.35),&#10;  2x small button. NET: cheaper, fewer holes, smaller box.&#10;&#10;OPEN ITEMS:&#10;- Bank B final 2 slots (after Jason&#39;s v0.11 audition).&#10;- Enclosure: 1590BB vs 125B at layout rough-in.&#10;- FREQ mod element: LED+LDR on 567 RT is the plan; verify&#10;  sweep range vs switched-cap ranges during breadboard." vertex="1"><mxGeometry height="620" width="410" x="2950" y="50" as="geometry" /></mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
